                            <div class="text-black/75 md:text-lg">
                                I’m a software engineer genuinely passionate about technology and how well-designed systems can solve real-world problems. Over the years, I’ve worked extensively with .NET and C#, building software that values clarity, scalability, and long-term maintainability. What really motivates me is not just making things work, but making them work well, with clean architecture, clear intent, and code that other humans can actually understand.
                                <br /><br />
                                I enjoy being involved in the full lifecycle of software development — from understanding the problem and designing the architecture to implementing, integrating, and shipping solutions. Lately, I’ve been diving deeper into cloud computing and modern distributed systems, exploring patterns that help applications scale naturally and remain maintainable over time. Learning is a constant for me, and this blog is part of that journey: a place to organize ideas, test concepts, and reflect on what I’m discovering along the way.
                                <br /><br />
                                Beyond code, I also spend a good part of my time mentoring developers and collaborating closely with teams. I believe the best solutions come from shared knowledge, honest discussions, and hands-on leadership. This space exists mainly to share experiences, lessons learned, and practical insights — not as a rulebook, but as an open notebook from someone who’s still curious, still learning, and still enjoying every step of the process.
